--- §5 artifact-cleanup + AUC bug fix pass: 2026-07-17 ---

Changes applied to jax-examples/src_01_domain_shift_toy.py:

  1. DATA INLINE (§5 requirement): toy_2d_4class.npz is now generated inline
     using gerar_gmm() with fixed seeds (PRNGKey(42) split into k_src, k_tgt).
     No file loading at runtime. The synthetic dataset was never a genuine
     external input — it is produced by this course's own code and must not be
     committed per §5.

  2. AUC BUG FIXED (genuine train/test leakage):
     Previous pass logged "AUC bug fixed" but the fix was INCOMPLETE.
     The function treinar_classificador_dominio trained on ALL 2400 points
     (source+target) and then evaluated AUC on those SAME 2400 training
     points. This is a train-set AUC (inflated and not a proper measure of
     generalizable domain-shift detection).

     Fix: Added sklearn train_test_split (stratified 80/20 split with
     random_state=SEMENTE). The MLP is trained on 80% (1920 points) and the
     AUC is computed exclusively on the held-out 20% test split (480 points,
     never seen during training). The ROC curve also uses the test split.

     Old AUC (train-set, inflated): 0.785
     New AUC (held-out test set):   0.749
     Both > 0.7, so the pedagogical conclusion is unchanged: shift is
     detectable. But the new value is an honest out-of-sample estimate.

  3. GENERATE-IF-ABSENT PATTERN for all checkpoints:
     Source model (nb1_encoder_source.pkl, nb1_head_source.pkl),
     target-only (nb1_encoder_targetonly.pkl, nb1_head_targetonly.pkl),
     SSDA (nb1_encoder_ssda.pkl, nb1_head_ssda.pkl):
     Each uses _checkpoints_ok(...) check. If PRETRAINED=True AND files exist
     → load. Otherwise → train inline AND save to assets/. This guarantees the
     notebook runs in a clean Colab where no assets are pre-committed.

  4. GENERATE-IF-ABSENT PATTERN for K-sweep:
     nb1_ksweep.npz loaded if present, else computed inline (5 K-values ×
     3 repeats × 400 epochs ≈ 15-20 s), then saved to assets/.

  5. GMM FIGURE FIX: Removed the erroneous `if PRETRAINED:` guard that
     caused PRETRAINED=False to try displaying a pre-generated PNG (missing
     in clean run). All figures now generate dynamically always.

  6. PNG FALLBACKS REMOVED: All `except: display(Image(ASSETS / "*.png"))`
     fallbacks depended on pre-generated PNGs that are gitignored and absent
     in clean runs. Removed: figures now generate directly (standard
     matplotlib), making the except branches unnecessary.

  7. GITIGNORE UPDATED: Added *.npz to root .gitignore (alongside existing
     *.png and *.pkl). All generated artifacts in jax-examples/assets/ were
     already covered by the jax-examples/assets/ rule; the new *.npz rule
     also blocks any accidental *.npz commits anywhere in the repo.

  8. ASSETS PATH: More robust ASSETS detection for Colab:
     try: pathlib.Path(__file__).resolve().parent.parent/"assets"
     except NameError: resolved "../assets" if parent is "jax-examples",
     else fall back to /tmp/nb01_assets (writable in any environment).
     ASSETS.mkdir(exist_ok=True, parents=True) called early in setup.

  9. MODULE-LEVEL HELPERS: carregar_pkl(), salvar_pkl(), _checkpoints_ok()
     defined at module level for reuse across cells.

